sentences: Dorothy Ann Collins (6 March 1933 – 22 September 1995), was an English folk musician, arranger and composer.
Born in Hastings, Sussex (now East Sussex), she grew up in an artistic, socialist, folk singing family.
By the late 1970s she retreated from touring and live concerts, and earned a living from gardening.
